summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council,
Recalling its relevant resolutions, particularly resolution 1494 (2003),
Having considered the Secretary-General's report of 14 January 2004,
Recalling OSCE summits' conclusions on Abkhazia, Georgia,
Deploring the lack of identification of perpetrators of the 2001 helicopter shooting,
Stressing the need for progress on a comprehensive settlement,
Welcomes the Secretary-General's report;
Reaffirms Georgia's sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity;
Supports the Secretary-General's efforts to promote stabilization and a comprehensive settlement;
Strongly supports the "Basic Principles for the Distribution of Competences between Tbilisi and Sukhumi";
Urges the Abkhaz side to consider this document and engage in constructive negotiations;
Regrets the lack of progress on political status negotiations;
Underlines the need for concessions from both sides;
Welcomes regular meetings of the Group of Friends in Geneva;
Urges parties to participate actively in task forces and working groups;
Welcomes a joint Georgian-Abkhaz visit to Bosnia and Herzegovina and Kosovo.
